  <prompt>
    Create integration tests for duplicate detection and idempotency. Test that
    the system correctly identifies duplicate emails/documents using content
    hashing and returns existing job IDs for idempotent requests.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    .NET developer specializing in integration testing. Expert in idempotency
    patterns and caching strategies.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Integration test suite validating duplicate detection works correctly and
    idempotent requests return cached responses.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Duplicate detection uses two mechanisms:
      1. Idempotency key (SHA256 of canonical request) with 24h Redis TTL
      2. Email content hash (HeadersHash) for logical duplicates
      Both must be tested to ensure users don't accidentally create duplicate
      artifacts.
    </background>
